shadcn primitives (Button, Input, Label, Select, Sheet, Dialog, Badge, Separator) live under `src/lib/components/ui/`. The `Button` accepts a `hotkey` prop (Cmd+letter from the reserved set `s u d e g b`, or the special string `Escape` for Cancel) and an optional `label` prop; together they wire the chord, an underlined-letter label, and a tooltip. **Cancel buttons use `hotkey="Escape"`** (bare Esc; bubble phase, defaults-prevented bail). Anchors (`href`) skip the dev-warn but can still take a hotkey. Full convention: [.cursor/rules/hotkeys.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/hotkeys.mdc).

## Patterns

- **Sheet vs Dialog vs dedicated page**: small/medium forms (≤~10 fields) → `Sheet` (full-screen on mobile, drawer on desktop). Confirmations and small pickers → `Dialog`. **Large forms (~20+ fields with junctions)** → dedicated page route (`/foo/new`, `/foo/[id]/edit`) with a presentational `<XForm>` component shared by both. The right-side drawer caps at `max-w-2xl` and gets cramped past about 10 fields; pages can use 2-col desktop layouts and breathe. See `book-form.svelte` + `/library/books/new` + `/library/books/[id]/edit` for the canonical full-page pattern.
- **Create + edit share one form/sheet**: take an optional `entity` prop; "create" mode = `entity == null`. See `time-entry-sheet.svelte` (sheet) and `book-form.svelte` (page-hosted).
- **Bindable props for v-model-style state**: `let { open = $bindable(false), value = $bindable<T[]>([]) } = $props();`
- **Form actions inside components**: use `use:enhance` and call back to the page via `onSaved` / `onSuccess` / `onError` callback props. For full-page forms also expose `onDirtyChange` so the host page can wire `beforeNavigate` for unsaved-edit confirmation.
- **Svelte 5 runes**: `$state`, `$props`, `$bindable`, `$derived`, `$effect`. Do not use Svelte 4 reactive `$:` syntax.
- **Heavy route-local sub-forms (bundle)**: if a child `.svelte` is large (bulk editors, uploads, barcode) but only mounts after a click or `bind:open`, **do not statically import it from the page** — use `import()` + a `$state` constructor holder (or `{#await import(...)}` inside the open gate). For `$effect`-driven preloads, gate with `browser` from `$app/environment` so SSR does not execute client-only dynamic imports. Reference: [025](mdc:docs/decisions/025-library-bundle-split.md), `/library/books/[id]/+page.svelte`, `book-form.svelte` + OL dialog.

## When to add a new component

- The pattern doesn't match any row in the inventory above
- A `.svelte` file exceeds ~150 lines
- The same JSX appears in 2+ pages

When you add one, update this rule.
